TERMSW-32011 Need simple wrapper tools written in C for calling scp and ssh with some secure syntax checking before calling the actual tool.  These will be called by

Specifically

- need to hardcode the -i parameter and key path being used
- Ensure nothing in any .ssh/ directory is used as an input
- Secure syntax that doesn't return a shell or allow anything besides executing the command

To compile the C code wrapper tool, do the following steps:

- make
- Commit in modem_key_ssh and modem_key_scp after you made code changes.

